node.title: Father charged with manslaughter of 3yo girl found in drain to stay in custody
node.alt: Flowers and stuffed animals marking a memorial at a fence in front of a body of water
node.description: The father of a young girl who was found unresponsive in a stormwater drain in north Queensland has not applied for bail.
node.content:
["A\u00a0Townsville man charged with the manslaughter of his three-year-old daughter will remain in custody.\u00a0", "Lawyers for the 27-year-old appeared in the Townsville Magistrates Court today and said there was no application for bail at this stage.", "Police said they were called to a Kelso property on Saturday night\u00a0after two children were reported missing.", "About 8.20pm, the three-year-old girl was found unconscious\u00a0in a stormwater drain and was transferred to Townsville University Hospital, where she was pronounced dead.", "", "
The little girl was found at the stormwater drain, but was pronounced dead at Townsville University Hospital.(ABC North Queensland: Travis Mead)
", "The\u00a0two-year-old boy was found wandering alone in a nearby street.", "Detectives from Townsville's Child Protection Unit have charged the man with one count of manslaughter, endangering children by exposure and driving under the influence of a drug.", "The matter is due to return to court for a committal mention in February next year."]
